# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok section of the new york times for tuesday , de scheduled to move by # p.m. et unless otherwise noted .
# ::alignments
(a / and
      :op1 (s / section
            :topic (t / time
                  :mod (c / country
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "New"
                              :op2 "York"))
                  :time (d / date-entity
                        :weekday (t2 / tuesday)))
            :ARG1-of (s2 / schedule-01
                  :ARG3 (b / by
                        :op1 (d2 / date-entity
                              :time "15:00"))))
      :op2 (n2 / note-01
            :polarity -
            :ARG1 s2
            :condition n2
            :polarity -
            :ARG1 (m / move-01)))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok share prices opened sharply higher on the tokyo stock exchange on thursday , the first trading day of this year , with the nikkei stock average rising ###.## points , or #.# percent , to ##,###.## in the first ## minutes of trading .
# ::alignments
(m / multi-sentence
      :snt1 (o / open-01
            :ARG1 (p / price-01
                  :ARG1 (s / share))
            :ARG2 (h / high-02
                  :ARG2-of (h2 / have-degree-91
                        :ARG1 p
                        :ARG3 (m2 / more
                              :degree (s2 / sharp))))
            :location (e / exchange-01
                  :ARG1 (s3 / stock
                        :mod (c / company
                              :name (n / name
                                    :op1 "Tkyo"))))
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (t / thursday)
                  :dayperiod (d2 / day
                        :ord (o2 / ordinal-entity
                              :value 1)
                        :part-of (y / year
                              :mod (t2 / this)))))
      :snt2 (r / rise-01
            :ARG1 (a / average-01
                  :ARG1 (s4 / stock
                        :mod (c2 / country
                              :name n
                              :op1 "Japan"))))
      :ARG2 (o3 / or
            :op1 (p2 / point
                  :mod (p3 / percentage-entity
                        :value "#."
                        :op2-of o3)))
      :time (t3 / trade-01
            :duration (m3 / multiple
                  :op1 (t4 / temporal-quantity
                        :quant 1
                        :unit (m4 / minute)))))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the xinhua a-stock index closed at #,###.## points tuesday , up ##.## points from the last close .
# ::alignments
(m / multi-sentence
      :snt1 (c / close-01
            :ARG0 (p / publication
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Xinhua"))
            :ARG1 (ii / index
                  :mod (s / stock)))
      :snt2 (p2 / point
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (t / tuesday))
            :ARG1-of (u / up-02))
      :snt3 (p3 / point
            :time (c2 / close-01
                  :mod (l / last))))

# ::id 3 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok iraqi government officials said tuesday they were quietly negotiating with leaders from the rebel-held city of fallujah to end a months-long standoff there and avoid a full-scale invasion to take it back from insurgents .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (g / government-organization
                        :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01
                              :ARG1 (c / city
                                    :name (n / name
                                          :op1 "iraqi"))))
                  :ARG2 (o / official)))
      :ARG1 (n2 / negotiate-01
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (p2 / person
                  :ARG0-of (l / lead-02
                        :ARG1 (c2 / city
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Fallujah")
                              :ARG1-of (h2 / hold-01
                                    :ARG0 (p3 / person
                                          :ARG0-of (r / rebel-01))))))
            :ARG2 (a / and
                  :op1 (e / end-01
                        :ARG0 p
                        :ARG1 (s2 / standoff
                              :duration (m / multiple
                                    :op1 (t / temporal-quantity
                                          :quant 1
                                          :unit (m2 / month)))
                              :location c2))
                  :op2 (a2 / avoid-01
                        :ARG0 p
                        :ARG1 (ii / invade-01
                              :ARG0 p
                              :ARG1 c2
                              :mod (f / full-scale)
                              :purpose (t2 / take-01
                                    :ARG0 p
                                    :ARG1 (ii2 / it)
                                    :ARG2 (ii3 / insurgent)
                                    :direction (b / back)))))
            :ARG1-of (q / quiet-04))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t3 / tuesday)))

# ::id 4 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok jakarta , april ## -lrb- xinhua -rrb- -- indonesian and u.s. air forces began on monday a five-day tactical airlift exercise , code-named '' cope west ## '' at halim <unk> air base , local media reported .
# ::alignments
(r / report-01
      :ARG0 (m / media
            :ARG1-of (l / local-02))
      :ARG1 (b / begin-01
            :ARG0 (a / and
                  :op1 (m2 / military
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Indian"
                              :op2 "Air"
                              :op3 "Forces"))
                  :op2 (m3 / military
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "U.S."
                              :op2 "Air"
                              :op3 "Forces")))
            :ARG1 (e / exercise
                  :mod (a2 / airlift-01)
                  :mod (t / tactic)
                  :duration (t2 / temporal-quantity
                        :quant 5
                        :unit (d / day))
                  :ARG1-of (n3 / name-01
                        :ARG2 (n4 / name
                              :op1 " cope"
                              :op2 "West"))
                  :location (b2 / base
                        :name (n5 / name
                              :op1 "Halim"
                              :op2 "Air"
                              :op3 "Base")))
            :time (d2 / date-entity
                  :weekday (m4 / monday)))
      :location (c / city
            :name (n6 / name
                  :op1 "Jakarta")))

# ::id 5 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok brazil got off to a dream start at the under-## world cup on sunday , with alan kardec scoring twice in a #-# win over costa rica .
# ::alignments
(s / start-01
      :ARG0 (t / team
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Brazil"))
      :ARG1 (g / game
            :name (n2 / name
                  :op1 "World"
                  :op2 "Cup")
            :mod (u / under))
      :ARG2 (o / off)
      :ARG1-of (d / dream-01)
      :time (d2 / date-entity
            :weekday (s2 / sunday))
      :ARG1-of (c / cause-01
            :ARG0 (s3 / score-01
                  :ARG0 (t2 / team
                        :name (n3 / name
                              :op1 "Alan"
                              :op2 "Kardec"))
                  :ARG2 2
                  :time (w / win-01
                        :ARG0 t2
                        :ARG1 (t3 / team
                              :name (n4 / name
                                    :op1 "Costa"
                                    :op2 "Rica"))))))

# ::id 6 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok australia on saturday defended its decision to temporarily stop processing asylum-seekers from afghanistan and sri lanka , saying its approach was legal and non-discriminatory .
# ::alignments
(a / and
      :op1 (d / defend-01
            :ARG0 (c / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Australia"))
            :ARG1 (d2 / decide-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (s / stop-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (p / process-01
                              :ARG0 c
                              :ARG1 (p2 / person
                                    :ARG0-of (s2 / seek-01
                                          :ARG1 (a2 / asylum))
                                    :source (a3 / and
                                          :op1 (c2 / country
                                                :name (n2 / name
                                                      :op1 "Afghanistan"))
                                          :op2 (c3 / country
                                                :name (n3 / name
                                                      :op1 "Sri"
                                                      :op2 "Lanka"))))
                              :duration (t / temporary))))
            :time (d3 / date-entity
                  :weekday (s3 / saturday)))
      :op2 (s4 / say-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (a4 / and
                  :op1 (l / legal-02
                        :ARG1 (a5 / approach-02
                              :ARG0 c))
                  :op2 (d4 / discriminate-02
                        :polarity -
                        :ARG0 c))))

# ::id 7 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok india 's embattled jammu-kashmir state has seen a spurt in the sales of mobile phones , which officials believe could help end the himalayan region 's alienation from the rest of india .
# ::alignments
(s / see-01
      :ARG0 (s2 / state
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Jammu-Kashmir")
            :location (c / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "India"))
            :ARG1-of (e / embattle-01))
      :ARG1 (s3 / spurt-01
            :ARG1 (s4 / sell-01
                  :ARG1 (p / phone
                        :ARG1-of (m / mobile-02))
                  :ARG0-of (h / help-01
                        :ARG1 (e2 / end-01
                              :ARG1 (a / alienate-01
                                    :ARG1 (r / region
                                          :mod (c2 / country-region
                                                :name (n3 / name
                                                      :op1 "Healayan")))
                                    :ARG2 (r2 / rest
                                          :part-of c)))
                        :ARG1-of (p2 / possible-01)))))

# ::id 8 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok ante razov and peter nowak each scored two goals as the chicago fire continued its offensive explosion by beating the miami fusion #-# .
# ::alignments
(s / score-01
      :ARG0 (a / and
            :op1 (p / person
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "ante"
                        :op2 "Razov"))
            :op2 (p2 / person
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "eter"
                        :op2 "nowak"))
            :mod (e / each))
      :ARG1 (g / goal
            :quant 2)
      :ARG2 (c / continue-01
            :ARG0 (f / fire
                  :mod (c2 / city
                        :name (n3 / name
                              :op1 "Chicago")))
            :ARG1 (e2 / explode-01
                  :ARG0 f
                  :ARG0-of (o / offense-02))
            :manner (b / beat-03
                  :ARG0 f
                  :ARG1 (f2 / fusion
                        :mod (c3 / city
                              :name (n4 / name
                                    :op1 "Miami"))))))

# ::id 9 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok the german government is now expecting a rise of only #.# percent in real gross <unk> product this year , german news agency dpa said on monday , quoting the government 's draft annual report on the economy .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (a / agency
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Dpa")
            :mod (n2 / news)
            :mod (c / country
                  :name (n3 / name
                        :op1 "Germany")))
      :ARG1 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 (g / government-organization
                  :ARG0-of (g2 / govern-01
                        :ARG1 c))
            :ARG1 (r / rise-01
                  :ARG1 (p / product
                        :ARG1-of (g3 / gross-03)
                        :ARG1-of (r2 / real-04)
                        :mod p))
            :ARG2 (p2 / percentage-entity
                  :value 1
                  :mod (o / only))
            :time (y / year
                  :mod (t / this)))
      :time (n4 / now)
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (m / monday))
      :manner (q / quote-01
            :ARG0 a
            :ARG2 (r3 / report-01
                  :ARG0 g
                  :ARG1 (e2 / economy)
                  :ARG1-of (d2 / draft-01)
                  :frequency (r4 / rate-entity-91
                        :ARG3 (t2 / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 1
                              :unit y)))))

# ::id 10 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok ukrainian president leonid kuchma said monday that he was `` satisfied '' with the results of last month 's nato summit , which he attended despite the alliance 's request that he stay away amid allegations that he approved the sale of a radar system to iraq .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Leonid"
                  :op2 "Kuchma")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (c / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "U.K."))
                  :ARG2 (p2 / president)))
      :ARG1 (s2 / satisfy-01
            :ARG0 (r / result-01
                  :ARG1 (s3 / summit
                        :mod (m / military
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "NATO"))
                        :time (m2 / month
                              :mod (l / last))
                        :ARG1-of (a / attend-01
                              :ARG0 p)))
            :ARG1 p
            :concession (r2 / request-01
                  :ARG0 (a2 / alliance)
                  :ARG1 (s4 / stay-01
                        :ARG1 p
                        :ARG3 (a3 / away)
                        :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
                              :ARG0 (a4 / allege-01
                                    :ARG1 (a5 / approve-01
                                          :ARG0 p
                                          :ARG1 (s5 / sell-01
                                                :ARG0 p
                                                :ARG1 (s6 / system
                                                      :mod (r3 / radar))
                                                :ARG2 (c3 / country
                                                      :name (n4 / name
                                                            :op1 "Iraq")))))))))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (m3 / monday)))

# ::id 11 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok kyle kinane is no stranger to playing for stand-up nerds , having toured nationally with indie comedy heroes such as patton oswalt -lrb- `` the comedians of comedy '' -rrb- and brian <unk> -lrb- `` mr. show '' -rrb- over the past two years .

      :polarity -
      :domain (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Kyle"
                  :op2 "Kinane"))

                        :mod (s2 / stand-up-07))))
      :ARG1-of (c / cause-01
            :ARG0 (t / tour-01
                  :ARG0 p
                  :ARG1 (n3 / nation)
                  :accompanier (h / hero
                        :mod (c2 / comedy)
                        :mod (ii / indie)
                        :example (a / and
                              :op1 (p4 / person
                                    :name (n4 / name
                                          :op1 "Patton"
                                          :op2 "Oswalt"))
                              :op2 (c3 / comedian
                                    :mod (c4 / comedy))))
                  :time (b / before
                        :op1 (n5 / now)
                        :duration (t2 / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 2
                              :unit (y / year))))))

                        :ARG0-of (o / oppose-01)))

                        :ARG0 (a4 / army)
                        :ARG1 (w2 / watch-01

# ::id 15 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred

      :ARG1 (d / dollar
            :mod (c / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Australia")))
      :ARG4 (l / level
            :ARG1-of (s2 / see-01
                  :polarity -
                  :duration (a / almost
                        :op1 (t / temporal-quantity
                              :quant 1
                              :unit (y / year)))))
      :time (w / wednesday)
      :ARG0-of (c2 / cause-01
            :ARG1 (b / burrow-01
                  :ARG1 d
                  :ARG4 (b2 / below
                        :op1 (m / monetary-quantity
                              :quant 100
                              :unit (c3 / cent)
                              :mod c
                              :name n
                              :op1 "United"
                              :op2 "States"))))
      :time (b3 / before
            :op1 (r / recover-01
                  :time (l2 / late))))

# ::id 20 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok china will increase the amount of export credit guarantees for domestic companies and cut premiums to help firms explore relatively untapped markets like latin america , the middle east and russia , china daily reports thursday .
# ::alignments
(r / report-01
      :ARG0 (c / country
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "China"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (ii / increase-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (a2 / amount
                        :quant-of (g / guarantee-01
                              :ARG1 (c2 / credit-02
                                    :mod (e / export-01))
                              :ARG2 (c3 / company
                                    :mod (d / domestic)))))
            :op2 (c4 / cut-02
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (p / premium)
                  :purpose (h / help-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (e2 / explore-01
                              :ARG0 (f / firm)
                              :ARG1 (m / market
                                    :ARG1-of (t / tap-02
                                          :polarity -
                                          :ARG2-of (r2 / relative-05))
                                    :example (a3 / and

                        :ARG1-of (f2 / fair-01)
                        :topic (a2 / and

                              :op2 (p2 / peace
